pageContext.description: Point broken off; edges chipped and rough; wings of blade very thin and rather sharp; a number of scratches on the surface apparently done in modern times with a rasp. Two rivet holes in socket.
pageContext.associations: ? Perhaps another spearhead (Class V), a bronze mace-head, and two iron daggers.
pageContext.collection: E.R.H. Dicken,c/o 37 St. Georges Road, Wimbledon, SW 19,(August 1938)
pageContext.site: England,Essex,Wormingford,According to Mr. Dicken, 2 iron daggers were reputed to have been found at Wormingford, and "perhaps with them" were found 2 Bronze spearheads (Class V) and this mace-head.
